<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Compliance with the request of the Chinese Foreign Minister referred to
                            in your April 4 does not involve formal recognition; it would be in
                            harmony with our de facto relations with the present administration. You
                            may instruct consuls to comply, with this understanding.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>